headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 36 points, Fred VanVleet added 20 points and a career-high 20 assists and the Toronto Raptors beat the undermanned Charlotte Hornets 128-108 on Sunday to secure a spot in the NBA play-in tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors beat Hornets, clinch play-in tournament spot

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges had 30 points and seven rebounds, helping the Brooklyn Nets move closer to clinching a playoff berth in the Eastern Conference by holding off the Utah Jazz 111-110 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets hold off Jazz 111-110, move closer to playoff berth

headlines.description: — The Memphis Grizzlies looked as though they were well on their way to yet another win. The Chicago Bulls had other ideas.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine, DeRozan lead surge as Bulls rally to beat Grizzlies

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Shaedon Sharpe scored 27 points, Kevin Knox II added 19 points and the short-handed Portland Trail Blazers beat the playoff-hopeful Minnesota Timberwolves 107-105 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sharpe scores 27 points, Trail Blazers edge Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Trae Young made two free throws with 1.8 seconds remaining in overtime to give Atlanta the lead and the Hawks beat the Dallas Mavericks 132-130 on Sunday night to keep pace in the Eastern Conference play-in race.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young lifts Hawks past Mavericks in OT, 132-130

events.name: Washington Wizards at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson and Quentin Grimes each scored 27 points, and the New York Knicks clinched a playoff berth with a 118-109 victory over the Washington Wizards on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks clinch playoff berth with 118-109 win over Wizards

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero and Wendell Carter Jr. had 14 points and nine rebounds each before sitting out the fourth quarter Sunday night in the Orlando Magic's 128-102 rout of the Detroit Pistons.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic hand Pistons 20th loss in 21 games with 128-102 win

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Doug McDermott scored 22 of his 30 points in the fourth quarter and overtime, and the San Antonio Spurs denied Sacramento a chance at clinching the Pacific Division with a 142-134 win over the Kings on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: McDermott scores 30 to lead Spurs past Kings 142-134

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis scored 40 points, LeBron James had 18 points, 11 assists and 10 rebounds to tie Jason Kidd for fourth place with his 107th triple-double and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Houston Rockets 134-109 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis has 40, James a triple-double as Lakers beat Rockets

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 35 points and the Phoenix Suns held off the Oklahoma City Thunder 128-118 on Sunday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 35 points, Suns roll past Thunder

headlines.description: — All-Star Donovan Mitchell scored 40 points and Evan Mobley had 14 points and 16 rebounds as the playoff-bound Cleveland Cavaliers pulled away late for a 115-105 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 40, Cavaliers power past Pacers 115-105

headlines.description: — Milwaukee coach Mike Budenholzer believes Giannis Antetokounmpo has done enough to merit a third MVP award.

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 26 points and blocked Klay Thompson’s 3-point attempt in the final seconds, and the Denver Nuggets held on for a 112-110 win over the Golden State Warriors on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores 26, Nuggets hold off Warriors 112-110
